text.tspan: The COLOR BAR shows the population weighted median
whereas the BRACKET BAR shows the IQR (25 - 75%tile range)
HOVERING over any component of the chart will show more details:
The COLOR shows the raw difference from the overall population (bottom row)
i.e. if the Overall Population median is 0.083 and the F60_MinCommute median is 0.062
the difference is -0.021 , which shows up as dark purple
The VERTICLE LINE additionally shows the median value for the overall population

tspan.tspan: i.e. If DA1 has an access score of 0.1 and 5 refugees and DA2 has an access score of 0.2 and 2
refugees, then the population weighted median is 0.1 whereas the raw median is 0.15.

text.tspan: All calculations use the POPULATION WEIGHTED MEAN specific to each subpopulation.
